headline: She became her family’s sole breadwinner at 11 — now she’s a world-famous perfume entrepreneur
summary: "I remember scraping the ice with my finger and looking out and thinking 'I've got to change my destiny,'" Ms Jo Malone CBE told CNBC's Steve Sedgwick.
